nhc_headline: ...OCTAVE BECOMES A POST-TROPICAL CYCLONE... ...THIS IS THE LAST NHC ADVISORY...
summary: ...OCTAVE BECOMES A POST-TROPICAL CYCLONE... ...THIS IS THE LAST NHC ADVISORY... As of 8:00 AM MST Thu Oct 09 the center of Octave was located near 17.7, -110.5 with movement ENE at 17 mph. The minimum central pressure was 1006 mb with maximum sustained winds of about 35 mph.
